description:
Job Responsibilities:

Take work from concept to final execution within deadline;
Understand marketing initiatives, strategic positioning and target audience; 
Communicate with clients & sales team in order to ensure the design meet customers' requirements;
Carry out graphic design and artwork production for printing Annual Report purposes as assigned; and
Perform digital design works including but not limited to design website’s visual imagery, graphics, animations and production of relevant digital photographs.

Job Requirements:

Design institute graduate or above;
5 years or above solid experience in graphic/ digital design field; 
Experience in the implementation of mobile/ responsive web layouts design would be advantageous;
Proficient in Adobe InDesign, Illustrator and Photoshop, MS Office;
Good command of both spoken Mandarin & Cantonese;
Self-motivated, responsible and detail-oriented;
A good teamwork player; and
Candidate with more experience will be considered for the position of  Assistant Art Director.

We offer competitive remuneration package. Interested parties please send full resume including date of availability, current and expected salary to HR Department, 2/F, 100QRC, 100 Queen’s Road Central, Hong Kong or by fax to 2523 7232 or by clicking apply now.

To understand more about EQUITY GROUP, please visit our website at http://www.equitygroup.com.hk

Data collected is for recruitment purpose only.

Our clients are now looking for high calibre candidates to fill the following positions:

Experience in proofreading/ translating documents;
Candidates who have interest in financial printing with no related experience are also welcome;
Proofread / translate financial documents including IPOs, Annual Reports and Circulars;
Ensure the timely delivery of production and projects;
Good bilingual ability in both English and Chinese;
Willing to take shift (roster will be arranged once a month) - with shift allowance.
Remarks:

Monthly salary: Open to discuss (depends on experience and skills + shift & OT allowance + discretionary bonus;
5-day work;
Working location: Central;
Working hours: 

For Proofreader: 3 shifts (7:30 am – 3:30 pm/ 3:30 pm – 11:30 pm/ 11:30 pm – 7:30 am)

For Translator: 2 shifts (10:00 am – 7:00 pm/ 2:00 pm – 11:00 pm)

Good fringe benefits e.g. banking holiday, medical, etc. will be provided.


If the above position is not suitable for you, please also feel free to send your CV to us for our job matching.

Interested parties please click "APPLY NOW" or send to OUR EMAIL and attach your updated resume with expected salary in "MS WORD" format.

Please quote the Job Ref. No. and Applied Post on the subject of your application.

